,Recommended,262260,19931911,"Posted: 25 December, 2015",all,Mrmotinjo,"This game is gawddamned awesome!Inspired by legendary SHMUPs (read: Tyrian), Jets'n'Guns is an explosive action horizontally scrolling destroy'em'up with a splendid soundtrack by Machinae Supremacy.It's based around Tyrian-like structure of progression, where you complete levels and upgrade your ship between them, with an option to pick up extra upgrades (and secret stuff!) during the levels. There's also an occasional boss you'll have to fight, as well as several unique levels where you zip around in your spacesuit instead of being in your ship. Also like in Tyrian and Raptor, you have a rather ample supply of armor (and repair options), so it's quite a bit more comfortable to play than the Japanese-type 1-hit-and-you-dead shoot'em-ups.The story is wacky and rather nonsensical, as are the weapon, level and enemy designs (there's a gun that literally shoots Superman clones, you pick up secret duckies along the way, and there's the borg-like alien race which is literally beer) and the game doesn't really take itself very seriously, but it creates a strangely interesting atmosphere which I really liked.It's hard as nails, too! Don't expect any hand-holding, and expect to die and restart levels- or even the entire game, because you CAN screw up your ship build and it WILL turn out to be impossible to complete later levels if you don't know what you're doing. I recommend playing on a lower difficulty level to begin with and get familiar with the game mechanics (which boil down to ""kill as many things as you can because you really need all the money you can get"").I'm really glad this game found its way on Steam- it has my full recommendation!"
