,Recommended,262260,8989220,"Posted: 5 February, 2014",all,ikke2902,"When I saw this on steam, I instantly bought it. I have completed the game at least 20 times (over 120 hour playtime) and still enjoying.This game is a side scrolling shoot them up game with lots of weapons, upgrades, enemies lots of hidden secrets en much more. What makes this shump so good? I will sum it up for you.Graphics/sounds/music:I love them all. Explosions are satisfying. Music are made from a real band!Enemies:A great variety of enemies. From tiny troops that you can kill by “touching” them with your ship to a horrific boss. During the game you will face pirates, aliens, mutants and even zombies! Ohh, zombies I really love them. There is a map with tons of them. They throw brains to you lol. Anyways in that map, you are willing to buy a tool “TV show cast” (can’t remember its name exactly). That tool will stream your killing action to the world as entertainment. For you as player, you will earn a  very nice amount of money for every multi kill. It goes from multikill (5 kills at once) to massacre (a lot of kills at once) to annihilation (name says all).Weapons:The amount of different weapons is massive. At some point, you can buy weapons that the bosses has used against you.  How amazing is that? Those weapons can be upgraded. Some weapons can be upgraded 3 times, other more than 6 times.  What I love in this game is, you will never lose your money. Every weapons/upgrades you bought, you can sell it back for the price you have bought.  It means, you can try any combo infinitely. Believe me, you will need it on normal difficulty already.Weapons has four categories: Front, rear, bombs and missileShips:These are really important. Different ships has different pros and cons. Some ships allows you to buy special tools, like ship repair, better shields, a time vortex to slow down the game on demand in hectic situation etc. Other ships allows you to carry more weapons from different weapon category (front, rear, and missile). Every ship has different amount of health/shield/heat sink.Secrets:There are many different secrets in this game to be discovered. There are secret maps, no spoiler on this. There are secret weapons. I love the tomato shooter and the baseball stick. Both awesome and useless at the same time. However, there are strong secret weapons ingame. Secret weapons cannot be bought. You can only get them by finding them on specific missions. If you want x times of a secret weapon, you need to complete game x times. Secret ship models, gotta love it. if you ever wanted to fly in a ship like one of the bosses you have faced. I wish you good hunting to this secret.Other nice things:In game, you can collect cargo that is locked. When you have finished the mission. You are willing to unlock these cargos. In order to unlock, you need to buy a Hacking tool. It is like a simplified mastermind game. Another nice thing is bounty hunter. You might catch a criminal. When you finished the game, you can do 2 things with him. Delivering him to the cops and claim the money prize or let the criminal bribe you. When you allow him to bribe you, you can get nothing or up to twice the money the cops are offering. Choose wisely…Almost finished.Replay value:You might be wondering why I completed the game more than 20 times and still playing.There are three things that increase the replay value.1) Every time you have completed a game, you will continue at mission 1 with a higher difficulty. You have read it right, you will CONTINUE. It means that you keep everything that you have unlocked/bought. That is nice, you can test if your strongest weapon can handle the normal difficulty.2) Even more powerful  weapons will only be unlocked when you play the game for the second time. These weapons are strong, but it comes with a price. You need to complete the game several times to get enough money to buy x times of it + fully upgrade them. This will keep you busy for a while.3) Did you found all secret maps, ships and weapons? You want x times of that secret weapon? Then you need to complete the game x times.Overall, this shump is highly customizable. Very nice replay value with many secrets that keeps you busy.  Something I really like.Gl hfNote: When you play this for the first time, I highly recommend easy difficulty."
