,Recommended,262260,23021025,"Posted: 16 May, 2016",all,DdCno1,"PresentationThis brilliant little 2D space shooter immediately hooks you with its fantastic heavy metal soundtrack byMachinae Supremacy.Have a listen!You can find the entirey soundtrack in .ogg format in the game's install folder(usually 'C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\SteamApps\common\JnG Gold\MUSIC' - may be different if you've chosen a different file path for Steam during Steam's installation or if you've chosen a different install path for this game).Speaking of metal, the amount of carnage and destruction you are able to unleash in this game is unlike anything I've ever seen. This title is worthy of its pounding, energetic soundtrack.Visuals may be low-res and 2D, but effects still look great and the amount of things going on at the same time on the screen is very impressive. Needless to say, this game runs on almost any machine made within the last fifteen years.GameplayJets'n'Guns is a very challenging game (even on easy), but thanks to the upgrade system being remarkably flexible and allowing for many different play styles, you can overcome its sometimes punishingly hard levels - you can just sell any item, weapon or upgrade without being financially punished and experiment with a new configuration. Incredibly tight controls, no matter if you're using keyboard, mouse, gamepad or joystick, also alleviate some of the difficulty. Level and enemy design are more creative and varied than anything you've ever seen (except for somewhat disappointing boss fights) and everything is neatly tied together by a completely insane story (but in a good way - the ending alone is ingenious).ConclusionJets'n'Guns is cheap, 100% bad♥♥♥♥♥ yet intelligent, has plenty of replay value and will forever be one of my favorite games."
76561198105843492,Recommended,262260,9248616,"Posted: 24 February, 2014",all,KuukerinNelli,"I am not too fond of ""old"" games but this one truly struck the chord with me.Jets'n'Guns Gold features a sidescrolling spaceadventure. Basicly what you need to do is to kill and destroy all enemies that fly at you. This is probably very usual in sidescrolling spaceadventure -games. Well what makes Jets'n'Guns stick out from the mass?Well in my opinion it's many things. Wide weapon arsenal, you've got many kinds of bombs, missiles, guns (even those are divided into smaller ""groups"", they aren't all just laser 1, laser 2...). You have different ships to choose from, you can collect new weapons and ships from the levels. You have ""secrets"" and secret levels ready for ""picking up"" scattered across the standard levels. You have several gadgets that you can use on your ship. Oh, and you can also upgrade almost everything you have purchased. I have probably missed some things here but that's my overall view on this, even though I haven't finished this game yet. One more thing I'd like to add - last but surely not least - when you buy something you can sell it back for FULL price. What this means is that you can test many sets of weapons and find the best for that particular level. ONE MORE! The music is just absolutely TERRIFIC! Same goes with the ""graphics"" or textures or what is it called. And the ingame jokes that are fitted in the ""background"" of the levels.Well, for the negative sides there are almost none. When I really push myself and try to come up with cons I mainly think of the fact that you can't choose the level you want to play like ""I want to play level 24, it had cool graphics and a fun boss.""That's about it folks. Hope you found this review helpful."
