,Recommended,262260,24191441,"Posted: 8 July, 2016",all,IHateSt3am,"I'm giving this a positive review, because i loved the original. If you’re going to pick this one up, play it on easy first.If your here for nostalgia, you’re not going to get it - or at least not all at once. This incarnation is much much much (much) more brutal than I remember. On your first play though, expect levels to last up to an hour of small step progression which mostly involves memory rather than skill. This is normal mode I’m talking about. Easy mode (""To fat to die"") is far too easy - I'm not crazy enough to even think about considering hard.There seems to be a lot more emphasis on ""strategy"" in this one too, whereas before, you could get away with choosing your favourite weapon loadouts, now you're going to be constantly swapping out to meet the level's brutally difficult requirements.This is an aspect I quite like, as it prevents you spam playing levels for gold for upgrades. Once a level is complete, that’s it for the current play though. What makes this ""strategy"" is that you can sell anything you buy for exactly the same amount, allowing you to truly explore all the possibilities of seizure-inducing neon-glowing jetting 'n' gunning."
