,Recommended,262260,8988234,"Posted: 5 February, 2014",all,Techbane,"It's been about a decade since this game was first released, and it's done a remarkable job standing the test of time. It does look somewhat out of date with a fixed resolution and no widescreen, but otherwise functions spiffingly, seems to map itself to Xinput controllers just fine, and most importantly, is still one of the most amazingly cathartic ""blow♥♥♥♥♥♥up"" scrolling shooters with an incredible soundtrack by Machinae Supremacy.The game's central mechanic is flying from left to right and shooting stuff. Make no mistake though, it is BALLS hard and even the first couple levels will seriously test your mettle. The upgrades system is very smartly designed, letting you sell off anything you don't need for full price, so you're always free to strip yourself down and try an entirely different loadout, which I strongly recommend if you don't feel like you're properly equipped for a level. If you're just dying repeatedly out of the gate, remember: enemy bullets are bad, colliding with stuff is EXTREMELY BAD.I only have a few real complaints. It's sometimes hard to tell foreground from background, which is especially critical because COLLIDING WITH STUFF IS BAD. There isn't much meaningful feedback for what's causing you the most damage (hint: it's usually colliding with stuff, that you may or may not notice), and a few of the more gimmicky stages are pretty aggravating. That said, I still love it."
