,Recommended,262260,9484299,"Posted: 14 March, 2014",all,GameDragonZero,"Jets'n'Guns is a mixture of bullet hell, reverse bullet hell (where you build your own insane firepower), ship customization, and your usual side-scroller.  Loud, crazy, brash, with plenty of enemies, guns, and weiredness, it's an extremely satisfying shooter.You play as . . . well the plot gets kind of bizarre, but sort of a soldier turned mercinary, who goes out to save the universe by blowing up spaceships, trucks, troops, building, jets, monsters, and everything else.  As you play you earn money, unlock equipment, find hidden weapons, and far, far more.  Eventually you're customizing your own spacecraft with all sorts of crazy weaponry as you find new ways to defeat your enemies.Customization and gameplay is a big part of this.  Pick the right loadout in order to survive, pick your battles, and react fast to survive.  The wrong loadout or bad tactics can kill you - and you may need to replay a level and/or recustomize your ship to get things right.  Fortunately, anything you buy can be traded in for full price, encouraging all sorts of combos.Pretty much a must-pick up for a side scroller/bullet hell player.  But a few caveats:1) The bullet hell aspect is also based around enduring attacks and being willing to take hits.2) At times the game screen can get crowded if you build your own bullet-spewing monstrosity, so don't just think a big loadout saves the day - you might not even be able to see your ship in all the chaos.3) The plot is utterly bizarre and it's hard to tell how much is parody, throwaway jokes, actual humor, or just plain craziness.  There's also some elements that may be parodies of sexist tropes, but the plots are so crazy it's hard to know."
