,Recommended,262260,14696589,"Posted: 28 February, 2015",all,Gemoron,"Do you know the feeling of nostalgica if you take an old game, start it and realize... it is still great?A game I played last week was such an experience: Jets'n'Guns.TL;DR: Jets'n'Guns is a great horizontal sidescroll shooter.The story is typical. You are a freelance hero taking jobs from suspicious people in bars untill you're called to safe the universe. This leads you through dozens of levels spread over different settings, ranging from killing everything, planetary setting, different cities, zombieinfested worlds to metal festivals. \m/The game is is held in 2D with good weapon animations and a great soundtrack delivered by the SID-Metalband Machinae Supremacy.The game has half a dozen of different ships and dizens of different weapons. Just taking the strongest weapon won't help in most missions because of the ships mechanics. Each ship has a ifferent number of weapon slots for missiles, bombs and front and back weapon slots. each weapon generates heat while firing, limiting the use of weapons so you can't simply keep firing all the time. You need to wait for the right moment to shoot or you'll be run over by the enemy as the enemy does know how to shoot back, or simply fly into you and kill you that way. This leads to tinkering over the right equipment for each level.Some levels end with bosses which require a special tactic each. Sadly most of them are equal to beat bosses in WoW: learn their attack pattern and evade their attacks, but stil, they are always challenging.I recommend Jets'n'Guns to all action game and arcade lovers. You can get a solid 6 hours of gameplay for 6 €, and after playing through once, you can restart the game with your current equipment. Sadly, the enemy strength isn't adjusted, but at least you can take revenge for all those miserable deaths.http://store.steampowered.com/app/262260/You can get it for 3,50€ + on ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥http://www.♥♥♥♥♥♥♥.net/category/11218/jets-n-guns-gold-steam-gift/"
