,Recommended,262260,20046655,"Posted: 28 December, 2015",all,cadillac20,"I've been playing this game for years and it's still one of the best shoot em ups I've ever played. What truly sets this apart from others like it are the weapons. You have dozens of weapons to customize your ship with and dozens upon dozens of combinations to experiment with. And each weapon feels different, whether it's in the weapons speed, style of destruction, or type of combat. Most of the fun you have will be from trying out the different weapons and finding the most effective ones to use. But beyond the weapons, everything else is top notch for an indie shooter, which is what has made the game such a classic over it's many years of being around. The art is great, the gameplay animation is excellent, the game is long with many levels to give you hours of entertainment. Of particular note are the writing, story, and music. The story and writing are silly, parodying most sci-fi, space operas, but it's still well written and entertaining to follow. And the music is one of the big standouts of the game. Created by Swedish metal band Machinae Supremacy, it's probably one of the best soundtracks for an indie action game I've ever heard, crafting a professional, well produced metal and electronic soundtrack. If you're a shoot em up fan and you haven't given Jets N Guns a try, you're missing out on a truly classic indie gem."
